♪ Their tears are filling up
Their glasses ♪

32:54.305 --> 32:56.557
♪ No expression ♪

32:56.641 --> 32:59.978
♪ No expression ♪

33:00.520 --> 33:05.066
♪ Hide my head
I wanna drown my sorrow ♪

33:05.149 --> 33:07.860
♪ No tomorrow ♪

33:07.944 --> 33:11.030
♪ No tomorrow ♪

33:11.406 --> 33:14.492
♪ And I find it kind of funny ♪

33:14.575 --> 33:17.203
♪ I find it kind of sad ♪

33:17.286 --> 33:19.664
♪ The dreams in which I'm dying ♪

33:19.747 --> 33:22.792
♪ Are the best I've ever had ♪

33:22.875 --> 33:25.503
♪ I find it hard to tell you ♪

33:25.586 --> 33:28.381
♪ I find it hard to take ♪

33:28.464 --> 33:30.842
♪ When people run in circles ♪

33:30.925 --> 33:33.594
♪ It's a very, very ♪

33:34.303 --> 33:37.682
-♪ Mad world ♪
-♪ Mad world ♪

33:39.934 --> 33:43.187
-♪ Mad world ♪
-♪ Mad world ♪

33:44.897 --> 33:45.773
Veronica.

33:49.986 --> 33:51.029
[crowd] Boo.

33:54.449 --> 33:57.326
-Boo.
-Boo!

34:05.209 --> 34:09.839
♪ Children waiting
For the day they feel good ♪

34:09.922 --> 34:12.675
♪ Happy birthday ♪

34:12.759 --> 34:16.220
♪ Happy birthday ♪

34:16.304 --> 34:21.017
♪ And I feel the way
That every child should ♪

34:21.100 --> 34:23.436
♪ Sit and listen ♪

34:24.020 --> 34:27.023
♪ Sit and listen ♪

34:38.701 --> 34:44.540
♪ And I find it kind of funny
I find it kind of sad ♪

34:44.624 --> 34:50.004
♪ The dreams in which I'm dying
Are the best I've ever had ♪

34:50.588 --> 34:55.718
♪ I find it hard to tell you
I find it hard to take ♪

34:55.802 --> 35:00.640
♪ When people run in circles
It's a very, very ♪

35:01.599 --> 35:05.436
♪ Mad world ♪

35:07.146 --> 35:08.856
♪ Mad world ♪

35:08.940 --> 35:09.982
Oh, my God.

35:18.407 --> 35:23.079
♪ Mad world ♪

35:28.334 --> 35:29.335
[FP applauding]

35:30.253 --> 35:31.295
[man] There he is.

35:31.379 --> 35:32.588
[crowd applauding]

35:33.756 --> 35:34.799
Quite the show.

35:35.716 --> 35:36.759
Thanks, Betty.

35:37.218 --> 35:38.177
Here you go.

35:41.556 --> 35:43.307
Let's give her a round of applause.

35:43.391 --> 35:44.725
[crowd cheering]

35:45.601 --> 35:49.480
Let's show her some of that
Serpent hospitality we're known for.

35:53.276 --> 35:58.406
You know what? I've been in and out of the
Serpents since I was younger than my son.

35:59.198 --> 36:00.575
And it's been a--

36:01.159 --> 36:02.451
A wild ride.

36:03.035 --> 36:05.955
Good times, bad times.

36:06.539 --> 36:10.918
But through it all,
the Serpents stuck by my side

36:11.002 --> 36:13.796
while most other people
turned their backs on me.

36:13.880 --> 36:15.548
My own family included.

36:16.966 --> 36:22.638
Now, the letter of the law says
that I can't be here in the Serpent den,

36:22.722 --> 36:27.560
that I can't associate with my friends,
my real family.

36:27.643 --> 36:29.020
-[man 1] Speak to it.
-[man 2] Yeah.

36:29.103 --> 36:30.021
My blood.

36:30.104 --> 36:32.064
-[man 3] Yup. Yup.
-[man 4] You're the man.

36:32.148 --> 36:34.150
But I've been thinking about that.

36:35.651 --> 36:38.237
And it'll be a cold day in hell

36:38.738 --> 36:42.116
before a snake
lets a pig tell him what to do.

36:42.200 --> 36:44.368
[crowd cheering]

36:45.036 --> 36:47.580
-Yeah.
-All right, Coyote Ugly. Let's go.

36:47.663 --> 36:49.790
-No, I'm staying. For Jughead--
-Elizabeth.

36:49.874 --> 36:52.543
-You're coming with me now.
-No. I'm staying.

36:53.836 --> 36:55.046
Well, I can't.

36:56.380 --> 36:59.008
Northside wants me out of this gang?

36:59.592 --> 37:04.764
Well, they better bring a coffin,
'cause FP Jones isn't retiring.

37:05.348 --> 37:08.643
I am not going gently into the night!

37:08.726 --> 37:10.311
I'm here to stay!

37:10.394 --> 37:12.146
So, bring the fire!

37:12.230 --> 37:14.482
-Bring the fire!
-Yeah!

37:14.565 --> 37:15.691
[crowd cheering]

37:32.917 --> 37:34.460
What happened to retiring?

37:39.006 --> 37:40.466
I know about the Snake Charmer.

37:41.509 --> 37:44.470
And the delivery you did,
and the debt you owe her.

37:45.137 --> 37:46.722
It was the one thing, son.

37:47.390 --> 37:49.725
The one thing I asked you not to do.

37:51.894 --> 37:56.816
-I can fix this. Let me just talk to her.
-No. No. I'm in, you're out.

37:57.650 --> 37:59.193
Penny's my problem now.

38:04.907 --> 38:06.575
You broke my heart, Jughead.

38:08.202 --> 38:10.579
-[man 1] Shots! Let's line them up!
-[man 2 howling]

38:13.958 --> 38:15.209
Yeah.

38:15.293 --> 38:17.878
-Hail to the king.
-[crowd] Hail to the king!

38:20.715 --> 38:21.549
Yeah.

38:22.425 --> 38:24.010
[crowd howling and cheering]

38:29.682 --> 38:33.811
Ronnie, what I said, it doesn't matter
if you don't wanna say it back to me.

38:33.894 --> 38:36.480
But it does. And it should.

38:37.398 --> 38:38.232
And...

38:39.275 --> 38:43.863
for whatever messed-up reason, Archie,
whatever deep-seated issues I have,

38:43.946 --> 38:46.198
I can't let myself go there with you.

38:50.661 --> 38:51.495
I'm sorry.

38:54.957 --> 38:56.083
I'm so sorry.

39:10.222 --> 39:11.223
Home, Andre.

39:11.974 --> 39:13.559
[Andre] Yes, Miss Veronica.

39:31.410 --> 39:32.661
Hey.

39:33.662 --> 39:35.831
What's wrong? Was it the dance?

39:37.208 --> 39:38.167
It's everything.

39:40.169 --> 39:43.255
And yeah. Why would you do that?

39:44.465 --> 39:46.550
I wanted to be a part of this.

39:47.134 --> 39:48.969
The Serpents, your world.

39:49.053 --> 39:49.929
Why?

39:51.222 --> 39:52.640
Archie knew to cut bait.

39:53.891 --> 39:57.478
Now I'm dragging you down.
I'm dragging my dad down.

39:57.561 --> 40:00.231
He's still figuring it out.
And it's gonna be okay.

40:00.314 --> 40:02.400
We'll figure out
what we have to do together.

40:02.483 --> 40:03.859
No, Betty. Mm-mm.

40:04.902 --> 40:05.736
Not together.

40:07.238 --> 40:11.158
Betty, if you stay, I don't know
if I can protect you anymore.

40:11.242 --> 40:14.036
You might get--
You probably will get hurt.

40:14.703 --> 40:16.539
I can't let that happen to you.

40:17.289 --> 40:19.458
-That's not your decision to make.
-Actually...

40:21.252 --> 40:22.294
yeah, it is.

40:24.672 --> 40:26.257
How many times, Jug?

40:27.758 --> 40:30.177
How many time are we gonna push
each other away?

40:30.261 --> 40:31.637
Until it sticks.

40:33.722 --> 40:37.143
That was my dad's one chance
at going straight, and I wrecked it.

40:37.226 --> 40:40.771
-I'm not going to destroy you, too.
-Just tell me what happened.

40:40.855 --> 40:42.731
Jug. Tell me what--?

40:44.066 --> 40:44.900
Please.

40:47.945 --> 40:48.821
Go home.

40:56.495 --> 40:57.955
[Jughead]  That night, I realized,

40:58.038 --> 41:01.584
it was like we'd been playing
a game of Snakes and Ladders.

41:01.667 --> 41:05.296
Me, Betty, Archie, Veronica.

41:05.379 --> 41:06.755
[Lewis Capaldi's "Bruised" playing]

41:06.839 --> 41:11.051
And in one fell swoop, we all slid off
the board and into freefall.

41:12.261 --> 41:13.554
And not just us.

41:13.637 --> 41:16.223
Other people, maybe innocent, maybe not,

41:16.307 --> 41:20.019
had been dragged into our game,
as old wounds reopened.

41:20.895 --> 41:22.438
[sighs]

41:22.521 --> 41:27.359
And as feelings
that had long been buried shook loose.

41:27.443 --> 41:30.029
♪ ...bruises that you left behind ♪

41:30.112 --> 41:34.366
♪ Oh, my lord, oh, my lord
I need you by my side ♪

41:36.702 --> 41:40.247
[Jughead]  And a boy looked out his window
at the girl next door.

41:40.664 --> 41:44.502
♪ 'Cause every day it's getting colder ♪

41:45.252 --> 41:48.380
♪ And if only I could hold you ♪

41:49.131 --> 41:50.341
♪ You'd keep my head... ♪

41:50.424 --> 41:54.011
[Jughead]  As if for the very first time.

42:31.173 --> 42:33.175
Subtitle translation by
Matt Duncan
